# Changelog

0.0.1 Repo essentials
0.0.2 package.json and initial oompsh.js
0.0.3 Basic working SSE server with example client
0.0.4 POST to ‘/notify’ to broadcast an event
0.0.5 Reads 'user:pass' from `process.env.OOMPSH_AUTH1` to `...AUTH9`
0.0.6 Switched from XMLHttpRequest to the Fetch API
0.0.7 Admin and Enduser both send via POST and listen for SSEs
0.0.8 Various UI improvements
0.0.9 Fix CORS: omit Fetch credentials, end OPTIONS requests
0.1.0 Replace OOMPSH_AUTH0 etc with OOMPSH_ADMIN_CREDENTIALS
0.1.1 Rename the demo Heroku app ‘https://oompsh.herokuapp.com’
0.1.2 Prefix API URLs with ‘v0/’
0.1.3 Sends SSE heartbeats every 10 seconds to keep TCP alive
0.1.4 Frontend persists INPUT values in cookies
0.1.5 Refactored shared code into ‘oompsh-lib.js’
0.1.6 OOMPSH.api and OOMPSH.action are in sync
0.1.7 oompsh-config.js (was oompsh-lib.js) built by config-builder.js
0.1.8 GET ‘/v0/’ responds with a description of the API
0.2.0 An admin’s SSE feed logs server state changes
0.2.1 Initial test.js with three basic `test_JSON_GET()` tests
0.2.2 Fairly complete tests, covering all API codes
0.2.3 POST ‘/v0/<creds>/test’ responds with test results
0.2.4 test.js checks that all codes used in oompsh.js have tests
0.3.0 test.js checks that all codes used in oompsh-config.js have tests
0.3.0 ‘/v0/begin/foo-bar,baz’ subscribes to ‘/v0/<creds>/add/baz’ etc
